    • Method Detail

      • getNumModelGroupIds

        public void getNumModelGroupIds(int modelNo,
                       int deviceId)
        Get the number of groups supported for a model. Response is MESSAGE_GROUP_NUM_GROUPIDS containing data:
        • EXTRA_MODEL_NO (byte)
        • EXTRA_NUM_GROUP_IDS (byte)
        Parameters:
        modelNo - The model number to query. Every model class defines its model number as the constant MODEL_NUMBER.
        deviceId - The id of the device to send the request to.

      • setModelGroupId

        public void setModelGroupId(int modelNo,
                   int groupIndex,
                   int instance,
                   int groupId,
                   int deviceId)
        Set the group id for a particular model. Response is MESSAGE_GROUP_MODEL_GROUPID containing data:
        • EXTRA_MODEL_NO (byte)
        • EXTRA_GROUP_INDEX (byte)
        • EXTRA_GROUP_ID (int)
        Parameters:
        modelNo - The model number to modify groups for.
        groupIndex - The group index within the model (max value found by calling getNumModelGroupIds)
        instance - The instance of the model on the device to modify (currently this field is ignored).
        groupId - The group id to write at the index.
        deviceId - The id of the device to send the request to.
